import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], errors='ignore')
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], errors='ignore')
    
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of Github activity during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    daily_avg = data.groupby('day')['count'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x='day', y='count', data=daily_avg)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average Github activity count per day?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
